    "summary": "This brief synthesizes ten expert analyses and a stakeholder stress-test on the future of small village primary schools in Hungary. Five policy scenarios are compared against what evidence actually supports, what remains genuinely uncertain, and what forty distinct argument clusters raised by modeled stakeholder interests demand in response. No scenario is recommended as 'the answer' — disagreement among experts and stakeholders is preserved throughout, because it reflects real, unresolved value conflicts and evidence gaps rather than a problem to be smoothed over.",
